# Observability Conventions

## Prometheus — metric naming

Pattern: `[domain]_[action]_[unit]`

```
# ✅ correct
scenario_runs_total          # counter — total runs
scenario_duration_ms         # histogram — duration
scenario_errors_total        # counter — errors by type
http_requests_total          # counter — all HTTP requests
db_query_duration_ms         # histogram — DB query time

# ❌ wrong
totalRuns                    # camelCase forbidden
run_count                    # missing domain prefix
scenarios                    # too vague, no action/unit
```

### Label conventions
- `status`: `completed` | `failed` | `pending` | `running`
- `type`: scenario type (e.g. `load_test`, `stress_test`)
- `method`: HTTP method lowercase (`get`, `post`)
- `route`: normalized path (`/api/scenarios/:id`, not the actual ID)

```ts
// ✅ correct label usage
scenarioCounter.inc({ type: dto.type, status: 'completed' });

// ❌ wrong — raw IDs as label values blow up cardinality
scenarioCounter.inc({ runId: run.id, status: 'completed' });
```

## Structured logs — JSON format

Every log call MUST pass an object. Never a plain string.

### Required fields
```ts
{
  event: string;      // snake_case verb_noun: 'scenario_started', 'db_query_failed'
  // + domain-specific fields
}
```

### Standard events per lifecycle
```ts
// Service method entry
this.logger.log({ event: 'scenario_run_start', type: dto.type });

// Success
this.logger.log({ event: 'scenario_run_complete', type: dto.type, durationMs: elapsed });

// Failure (in catch)
this.logger.error({ event: 'scenario_run_failed', type: dto.type, error: message });
```

### Forbidden log patterns
```ts
// ❌ plain string — unparseable in Loki
this.logger.log('scenario started');
this.logger.log(`running ${dto.type}`);

// ❌ object without event field — unqueryable
this.logger.log({ type: dto.type, id: run.id });

// ❌ logging sensitive data
this.logger.log({ event: 'user_login', password: dto.password });
```

## Sentry — when to capture

| Situation | Action |
|-----------|--------|
| Unhandled exception in service | `Sentry.captureException(err, { tags, extra })` |
| Expected business error (404, 400) | Do NOT send to Sentry |
| External service timeout | `Sentry.captureException` with `tags.service` |
| DB connection failure | `Sentry.captureException` with `tags.layer: 'db'` |

```ts
// ✅ correct — unexpected error with context
} catch (err) {
  Sentry.captureException(err, {
    tags: { domain: 'scenarios', type: dto.type },
    extra: { runId: run.id },
  });
}

// ❌ wrong — no tags (unfilterable in Sentry dashboard)
Sentry.captureException(err);

// ❌ wrong — sending expected errors
throw new NotFoundException('run not found');  // do NOT also captureException here
```
